---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about Blackout Pickleball — a diversity and inclusion pickleball community celebrating Black representation in the sport.">

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-surface">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p class="text-accent font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Our Story</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight">Celebrate Diversity.<br />Play with Purpose.</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg mx-auto">
        <p class="text-text-light text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Blackout Pickleball was founded with a bold vision: to create a vibrant, inclusive space in the fastest-growing sport in America. We are dedicated to increasing Black representation in pickleball while welcoming and encouraging everyone — regardless of background — to join us in playing, supporting, and sharing the game.
        </p>

        <p class="text-text-light text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6">
          Our high-performance gear is crafted from a premium 85% Polyester and 15% Spandex blend. Designed to release heat and wick moisture, our breathable 4-way stretch fabric ensures perfect shape recovery and extreme freedom of movement on the court.
        </p>

        <p class="text-text-light text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6">
          Whether you're on the court for a casual game or a competitive match, Blackout Pickleball provides the performance gear and community you need to play your best.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Founder Section -->
      <div class="mt-16 bg-blackout text-text-inverse rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">Meet the Founder</h2>
        <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          Jonathan Dapaah founded Blackout Pickleball to bridge the gap between high-performance sport and cultural representation. A passionate pickleball player himself, Jonathan saw an opportunity to bring more diverse voices and energy to the court — and the gear to match.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
